16/12/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR conducted inspections at several military facilities in Han Pjesak in eastern Republika Srpska Thursday (16 December), according to media reports. 
A EUFOR spokesman confirmed the surprise operation, saying details would be presented later.
In other news, US war crimes envoy Pierre-Richard Prosper said Wednesday that war crime indictees Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic should be tried by The Hague and not by Serbian courts, as Belgrade officials have suggested.
Also Wednesday, UN war crimes tribunal spokesperson Florence Hartmann denied that former Bosnian Serb Army General Vinko Pandurovic -- whose location in Serbia and possible surrender have been the subject of speculation -- was extradited to The Hague Tuesday. 
(Beta, Danas, Fena - 16/12/04)
